---
# === Forward Plan ===
#
# Goal: Enable all checks in these categories (unless in Intentionally Disabled):
#   bugprone-*, cppcoreguidelines-*, misc-*, modernize-*, readability-*
#
# === Disabled Check Groups ===
#
# Irrelevant platforms/frameworks:
#   abseil-*, altera-*, android-*, darwin-*, fuchsia-*, google-objc-*,
#   linuxkernel-*, llvm-*, llvmlibc-*, openmp-*, zircon-*
#
# Run separately:
#   clang-analyzer-*  (dedicated scan with report)
#
# === Evaluated ===
#
# bugprone-branch-clone:
#   Attempted, no fixit, lots of violations.
#
# bugprone-unchecked-optional-access:
#   Attempted, no fixit, lots of violations. Extensive usage of std::optional in this codebase.
#
# cppcoreguidelines-init-variables:
#   Attempted, has fixit, results in massive diff. Somewhat desireable for ND avoidance.
#
# === Intentionally Disabled ===
#
# bugprone-sizeof-expression:
#   Attempted, no fixit, developers rejected stating lack of value.
#
# concurrency-mt-unsafe:
#   Attempted, no fixit, may not be realistic to fix as it flags std::getenv();
#
# performance-avoid-endl:
#   Attempted, but developers rejected auto-fixits due to concerns about
#   potential flush dependency.
